favorites.content: We must be as courteous to a man as we are to a picture, which we are willing to give the advantage of a good light.
favorites.author: Ralph Waldo Emerson

favorites.content: People don't notice whether it's winter or summer when they're happy.
favorites.author: Anton Chekhov

favorites.content: If I were two-faced, would I be wearing this one?
favorites.author: Abraham Lincoln

favorites.content: Accept the things to which fate binds you and love the people with whom fate brings you together but do so with all your heart.
favorites.author: Marcus Aurelius

favorites.content: Whenever you find yourself on the side of the majority, it is time to pause and reflect.
favorites.author: Mark Twain

favorites.content: The inherent vice of capitalism is the unequal sharing of blessings; the inherent virtue of socialism is the equal sharing of miseries.
favorites.author: Winston Churchill

favorites.content: Sir, my concern is not whether God is on our side; my greatest concern is to be on God's side, for God is always right.
favorites.author: Abraham Lincoln

favorites.content: He has no enemies, but is intensely disliked by his friends.
favorites.author: Oscar Wilde

favorites.content: You need chaos in your soul to give birth to a dancing star.
favorites.author: Friedrich Nietzsche

favorites.content: Nothing strengthens authority so much as silence.
favorites.author: Leonardo da Vinci

favorites.content: But man is not made for defeat. A man can be destroyed but not defeated.
favorites.author: Ernest Hemingway

favorites.content: Wherever a man may happen to turn, whatever a man may undertake, he will always end up by returning to the path which nature has marked out for him.
favorites.author: Johann Wolfgang von Goethe

history.content: Stay positive and happy. Work hard and don't give up hope.

history.content: Every day may not be good, but there is something good in every day.

history.content: Winners never quit and quitters never win.

history.content: Cunning... is but the low mimic of wisdom.
history.author: Plato
